OL,3,CWarning after children dig huge hole
OL,4,Con Cornwall beach
OL,6,FResponding to the hole, a spokesperson
OL,7,Ffor the Coastguard said: "These
OL,8,Fcollapses are rare but can be lethal
OL,9,Fif you become trapped in one.
OL,11,F"There's nothing wrong with digging
OL,12,Fholes at the beach and filling them
OL,13,Fwith water for your kids to play in.
OL,15,F"But please be aware of the risks of
OL,16,Fdigging larger holes and tunnels when
OL,17,Fat the beach."
OL,19,FIt is the second time a large hole has
OL,20,Fbeen discovered on a beach in Cornwall
OL,21,Fthis summer.
